where Δ&quot;X&quot; := [&quot;idX&quot;] denotes the diagonal of &quot;X&quot; × &quot;X&quot;, is a functor. The motive [&quot;X&quot;] is often called the &quot;motive associated to the variety&quot; X.

As intended, Choweff(&quot;k&quot;) is a pseudo-abelian category. The direct sum of effective motives is given by

