The tensor product of morphisms may also be defined. Let &quot;f&quot;1 : (&quot;X&quot;1, &quot;α&quot;1) → (&quot;Y&quot;1, &quot;β&quot;1) and &quot;f&quot;2 : (&quot;X&quot;2, &quot;α&quot;2) → (&quot;Y&quot;2, &quot;β&quot;2) be morphisms of motives. Then let &quot;γ&quot;1 ∈ &quot;A&quot;(&quot;X&quot;1 × &quot;Y&quot;1) and &quot;γ&quot;2 ∈ &quot;A&quot;(&quot;X&quot;2 × &quot;Y&quot;2) be representatives of &quot;f1&quot; and &quot;f2&quot;. Then

